## API Response Envelope

Every API response follows this structure:
```typescript
interface ApiResponse<T> {
  success: boolean;
  data?: T;
  error?: string;
  message?: string;
}
```

For paginated responses:
```typescript
interface PaginatedResponse<T> extends ApiResponse<T[]> {
  meta: {
    page: number;
    limit: number;
    total: number;
    totalPages: number;
  };
}
```

## Date Handling Rule

- **Always store UTC** in the database (DateTime fields)
- **Convert to user timezone** in the response layer only
- Use `date-fns` and `date-fns-tz` for all date operations
- **Never use moment.js** (see DO NOT list)
- Time strings in Schedule (HH:MM format) are interpreted relative to the schedule's timezone

## Error Handling Rule

- Centralized `AppError` class extending `Error` with `statusCode`, `code` (enum), `isOperational`
- `asyncHandler` wrapper on **every** async route handler
- Use Pino logger for all server-side logging
- **Never `console.log` in route handlers** — use `logger.info/warn/error`
- Global error handler middleware catches all errors and returns `ApiResponse` format

## Validation Rule

- Zod schema defined **first** for every endpoint (in `types/schemas/`)
- Validated in middleware (via `validate()` factory) **before** controller runs
- Controller can trust that `req.body`/`req.query`/`req.params` are valid typed data

## Environment Variable Rule

- **All** `process.env` access goes through `config/env.ts` only
- Validated with Zod at startup
- **Fail fast** — server refuses to start if any required env var is missing
- Never reference `process.env.XYZ` outside of `config/env.ts`
- **Integration credentials (Google, Zoom, Microsoft, etc.) are NOT in .env** — they are stored encrypted in the database via the dynamic App Store

## Integration Architecture (Dynamic App Store)

- Integrations follow a **marketplace/app-store model** (like Cal.com)
- `App` table defines available integration providers (Google Calendar, Zoom, Microsoft Teams, etc.)
- App credentials (client_id, client_secret) stored **encrypted** in the `App` table using AES-256-GCM
- Users "install" apps via the UI, triggering OAuth flows — user tokens stored in `IntegrationToken` table (also encrypted)
- New integrations can be added via admin settings UI — no code deploy or .env changes needed
- Only `ENCRYPTION_KEY` stays in .env as the master encryption secret

## Database Rules

- **UUID primary keys** on every table
- **`created_at`** and **`updated_at`** on every table (auto-managed)
- **Soft deletes** via `deleted_at` (nullable DateTime) where specified
- Use `prisma.$transaction` for multi-table writes
- **Indexes** on all FK columns and query-critical fields (email, username, slug, status, start_time)
- Column defaults: `uuid()` for id, `now()` for created_at, `@updatedAt` for updated_at

## DO NOT List

- ❌ **No moment.js** — use date-fns
- ❌ **No axios on backend** — use native fetch (Node 18+)
- ❌ **No default exports** except Next.js pages/layouts (required by framework)
- ❌ **No `var`** — use `const` or `let`
- ❌ **No raw SQL** unless commented with detailed reason
- ❌ **No `console.log`** in production code — use Pino logger
- ❌ **No inline styles** in React — use Tailwind utilities
- ❌ **No CSS modules** — Tailwind only
- ❌ **No direct `fetch()` in React components** — use TanStack Query hooks

## Auth Strategy

- Full JWT auth flow (register, login, refresh, logout)
- Frontend auto-logs in with default credentials on first visit (bypass mode)
- Default user is seeded in database
- Access token: 15 min expiry, stored in memory
- Refresh token: 7 days expiry, stored in httpOnly cookie + DB (hashed)
- Refresh token rotation on every refresh

## Theme System

- User-configurable theme (light/dark mode)
- Default: dark mode (matching Cal.com reference screenshots)
- Theme preference stored in localStorage + user profile
- CSS variables for theme tokens, toggled via class on `<html>`
